    <h2> 1. Student Details </h2>

    <p>(a., b.) When completing the student Form, fill out your first name surname and university student number in the
        fields provided.<br>
        <br>
        (c.) Your student number is the nine-digit number found on the front of your student ID.<br>
        <br>
        (d.) To select the Student Type and Year of Study, select the field and a dropdown menu will appear for you to
        select the option relevant to you.<br>
        <br>
        (e.) The E-mail address entered must be your university email ending @student.le.ac.uk<br>
        <br>
        Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.</p>
        <br>
    <h3>(2) Placement Provider Details Section</h3> (2ab., 2ac.) In the fields provided enter the location your
    placement will be based. Contact your placement provider for clarification if needed.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    (2b.) In the fields provided enter the contact information of a member of your placement provider's team. This could
    be a recruitment officer, including HR, or your manager.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(3) Placement Role Details</h3> (3bii., 3c.) To enter the dates, you can click on each number in the fields to
    add the dates manually or click on the calendar icon to navigate through and select dates using the arrows.<br>
    <br>
    (3d.) To enter your working hours, select the field and manually enter the number of hours. Use the up and down
    arrows on the right to add or subtract 0.01 hours to the time.<br>
    <br>
    (3e., 3g., 3h.) Select the field and a dropdown menu will appear for you to select the option relevant to you.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(4) Work Factors</h3> (4a.) Select the field and a dropdown menu will appear for you to select the option
    relevant to you.<br>
    <br>
    (4c.) If clarification is needed as to why, contact your placement provider.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(5) Transport and Travel Factors</h3> (5a.) To choose a mode of transport scroll through the field using your
    mouse or scroll bar. Your selected option will be highlighted in orange. If you select other, an additional input
    box will appear for you to specify.<br>
    <br>
    (5b., 5d., 5e.) Select the field and a dropdown menu will appear for you to select the option relevant to you.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(6) Location and Regional Factors Section</h3> (6a., 6b., 6c.) Select the field and a dropdown menu will appear
    for you to select the option relevant to you.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(7) Health and Environmental Factors</h3> (7b.) The SafeZone App can be downloaded on both Android and iOS
    devices.<br>
    <br>
    (7c.) <a href="https://www.gov.uk/global-health-insurance-card"> Link to Apply</a> <br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
    <h3>(8) Personal Factors Section</h3> (8a.) Select the field and a dropdown menu will appear for you to select the
    option relevant to you.<br>
    <br>
    Once all fields have been entered, click on the Submit button at the bottom of the page.<br>
    <br>
